While average usage is very low, a single recorded peak of 874.80 Mbps temporarily exceeded the 500 Mbps provisioned limit. This event was extremely brief (1 minute exceeding 90% capacity) and does not represent typical congestion. Overall SLA compliance is excellent.

**Conclusion**
The link is vastly over-provisioned and should be downgraded. A new provisioning target of 9 Mbps is recommended.
